AB  - The economically, socially, and culturally most developed areas worldwide are located predominantly along the coastlines. Socioeconomic development has accumulated large populations and high value assets in coastal cities while coastal cities have become prone to climate change effects. Sea level rise, tropical cyclones, rainstorms, floods, storm surges, high temperatures, and heat waves have posed new challenges to coastal city development. Domestic and foreign coastal cities such as Shanghai, Guangzhou, Tianjin, Xiamen, Hong Kong, New York, London, Tokyo, Sydney, Venice, Singapore, and Cape Town are analyzed on their current climate change adaptation techniques. Measures are compared and future challenges for adaptation are assessed. Â© 2014 by Koninklijke Brill nv, Leiden, The Netherlands. All rights reserved.
