TI  - Coastal communities and ITQ management. The case of Icelandic fisheries
PY  - 1996
VL  - 36
IS  - 2
AB  - Fisheries management by individual transferable catch quotas is being promoted as an idea basis for sustainable development in the fisheries. In Iceland, where ITQs have been introduced along with other free marker oriented policies, quota holdings ?re being concentrated on trawler companies and there has lately been a major build-up of offshore fishing capacity, The inshore fleet is being reduced, and many fishing communities are suffering from substantial loss of quota shares. The distributional effects of ITQ management are extensive, and it may be called into question whether the Icelandic fisheries are moving towards sustainable development.
